@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About - InventoryHub</PageTitle>

<h1 class="mb-2">ℹ About InventoryHub</h1>

<p class="text-muted mb-4">
    InventoryHub is a full-stack inventory management application developed using
    Blazor WebAssembly and ASP.NET Core Minimal API.
</p>

<div class="row g-3">

    <div class="col-lg-6">

        <div class="card shadow-sm h-100">

            <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">

                <strong>Technology Stack</strong>

            </div>

            <div class="card-body">

                <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">

                    <span class="badge bg-primary p-2">Blazor WebAssembly</span>
                    <span class="badge bg-success p-2">ASP.NET Core</span>
                    <span class="badge bg-info text-dark p-2">Minimal API</span>
                    <span class="badge bg-warning text-dark p-2">C#</span>
                    <span class="badge bg-secondary p-2">Bootstrap 5</span>
                    <span class="badge bg-dark p-2">System.Text.Json</span>

                </div>

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-6">

        <div class="card shadow-sm h-100">

            <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">

                <strong>Project Features</strong>

            </div>

            <div class="card-body">

                <ul class="mb-0">

                    <li>REST API Integration</li>
                    <li>Nested JSON Responses</li>
                    <li>Product Management</li>
                    <li>Shared Models</li>
                    <li>Error Handling</li>
                    <li>Performance Optimization</li>
                    <li>Memory Cache</li>
                    <li>CORS Configuration</li>

                </ul>

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

</div>

<div class="card shadow-sm mt-4">

    <div class="card-header bg-dark text-white">

        <strong>Microsoft Copilot Contribution</strong>

    </div>

    <div class="card-body">

        <table class="table table-hover align-middle">

            <thead>

                <tr>

                    <th style="width:30%">Project Phase</th>

                    <th>How Copilot Helped</th>

                </tr>

            </thead>

            <tbody>

                <tr>

                    <td>Integration</td>

                    <td>Generated and refined communication between the Blazor client and Minimal API.</td>

                </tr>

                <tr>

                    <td>Debugging</td>

                    <td>Resolved API route updates, CORS configuration, and JSON deserialization issues.</td>

                </tr>

                <tr>

                    <td>JSON</td>

                    <td>Created nested Category objects and validated API response structure.</td>

                </tr>

                <tr>

                    <td>Optimization</td>

                    <td>Suggested shared HttpClient configuration, in-memory caching, and cleaner code organization.</td>

                </tr>

            </tbody>

        </table>

    </div>

</div>

<div class="alert alert-primary mt-4">

    <h5 class="mb-2">Project Summary</h5>

    <p class="mb-0">

        InventoryHub demonstrates modern full-stack web development using
        Blazor WebAssembly and ASP.NET Core Minimal API. The application
        showcases API integration, structured JSON communication, optimized
        performance, reusable models, and Microsoft Copilot-assisted
        development.

    </p>

</div>